<H3> <TI>   Cossacks Support Draft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cossacks Support Draft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904164594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1511 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [by ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 19 TASS -- "We, Cossacks, a people of 
Russia, have always served for the interests of the Russian 
state, protected the inviolability of its borders and been a 
guarantor of internal stability of society. 
  "A meeting of atamans of the Union of Troops of Russia and 
abroad held on April 16 in the historical capital of Cossack 
troops - the town of Novocherkassk, approved the draft agreement 
on achievement of civic accord in Russia," says a statement of 
the Union of Russian and Foreign Cossack Troops sent to Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin. 
  The Union of Cossack Troops of Russia and abroad is ready to 
sign the agreement on "the basis of mutual respect to different 
outlooks, political convictions, ethnic and cultural traditions 
and human rights, and carry its share of responsibility for the 
implementation of the agreement," says the document. 
  The statement was reported by the Russian president staff's 
information center. 

</TEXT>

