<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   PCD's New Tactics To Fight Fascists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PCD's New Tactics To Fight Fascists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1904125094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK1904125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed POSFACTUM report in the "In Brief" column] </F>
  [Text] Moscow -- On 20 April the Party of Constitutional 
Democrats (PCD) will hold a press conference at the 
International Moscow Press Club, subject: "New Order." 
According to party chairman Viktor Zolotarev, the press 
conference is going to hear the PCD leadership announce a change 
in its methods of political activity. As of now the PCD will 
rely on populism and scandal. "We are going to fight fascism 
with its own weapons, and we hope to do this as early as this 
year," V. Zolotarev stated. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

