<F P=106> ["Own information" report: "TRETYE SOSLOVIYE Continues To </F>
Live..."] 
  [Text] Publication of the newspaper TRETYE SOSLOVIYE 
[third estate], founded by Aleksey Adzhubey [Khrushchev's 
son-in-law] shortly before his untimely death, has been resumed 
with the appearance of issue No. 12. The newspaper, as is clear 
from its name, is aimed at representatives of the nascent estate 
of Russian entrepreneurs and attempts to fulfill the active 
function of their enlightener. 
  After issue No. 11 the founders and the editorial board got 
into financial difficulties (the newspaper does not receive 
state subsidies). The "debts" to subscribers are now being 
repaid. 
  In the present issue the reader will be attracted, above 
all, 
to a double-page spread of previously unpublished photographs of 
N.S. Khrushchev from R.N. Adzhubey's personal archive with her 
own comments and reminiscences (pegged to Khrushchev's 
centenary), as well as a number of articles by well known 
political experts and economists devoted to the most painful 
problems of Russian society. 

</TEXT>

