<H3> <TI>   Favors Defense Spending Cut </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Favors Defense Spending Cut </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004095294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yegor Gaydar, leader of the parliamentary group 
Russia's Choice, believes the country's budget expenditure on 
defense should be cut. In an interview for DELOVOY MIR, he 
noted that 37 trillion rubles have been earmarked in the draft 
budget for military spending; in other words a fifth of the 
budget. Yegor Gaydar believes it necessary for the Russian Army 
to be tailored to the new conditions and new possibilities that 
exist in the country. 

</TEXT>

