<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "New Excise Rate Per Tonne of Oil Sold"] </F>
  [Text] As of 1 May this year the Russian Government is 
establishing an excise rate for extracting enterprises of, on 
average, 14,750 rubles per tonne of oil, including gas 
condensate. This amount will change monthly, depending on the 
change in the rate of the ruble against the U.S. dollar. There 
will be different rates for individual oil and gas extracting 
enterprises. 

</TEXT>

