<H3> <TI>   `Special Service' Chiefs Sign Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Special Service' Chiefs Sign Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004102094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0924 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Andrey Palariya] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- Sergey Stepashin, director of the 
Russian Federal Counterintelligence Service (FSK), and Aleksandr 
Korzhakov, chief of the Russian Federation president's Security 
Service, exchanged views at a meeting today on cooperation 
between and coordinating the activity of the two special 
services to ensure the safety of the Russia president and state 
security as a whole. 
  The ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from the FSK that 
today's 
meeting was not caused by any extraordinary events. It was held 
within the framework of establishing collaboration between the 
counterintelligence service and other Russian special services 
in order to eradicate the duplication of work. 
  Sergey Stepashin and Aleksandr Korzhakov signed an agreement 
which lays down the legal and contractual basis for cooperation 
between the two special services in operational investigation 
work, and which envisages the regular exchange of information. 
  Earlier, a similar agreement was signed between the FSK and 
the Foreign Intelligence Service. 

</TEXT>

