<H3> <TI>   Pacific Fleet To Stop Utilities Disconnection </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pacific Fleet To Stop Utilities Disconnection </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004042894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0338 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yuriy Grachev] </F>
  [Text] Vladivostok, 20 Apr -- The Commander of the Pacific 
Fleet Admiral Georgiy Gurinov has issued an order to post armed 
guard at the fleet's water mains and power grids in the garrison 
in Petropavlovsk-Kamchatskiy and to stop any attempts of local 
authorities to disconnect military installations from these 
services. The press center of the Pacific Fleet reports that 
this decision has been prompted by a recent warning issued to 
commanders of military units stating that their water and power 
will be cut off due to the arrears in payments which have now 
reached 4.5 billion rubles. 
  At the sanction of the head of the town administration, an 
attempt was undertaken to disconnect water and power from the 
headquarters and other units of the Kamchatka flotilla. The 
military quickly retaliated by posting armed guards. As a 
result, the town authorities are in trouble. To add insult to 
injury, an attempt of duty managers to disconnect the supply was 
stopped by a preventive gunshot of the guard. 

</TEXT>

