<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Nuclear Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Edict on Spring Draft, Discharge </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Edict on Spring Draft, Discharge </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2004092894 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2004092894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 784 of the Russian Federation president "On the </F>
Draft of Citizens of the Russian Federation for Military Service 
in April-May 1994 and the Discharge of Soldiers, Seamen, 
Noncommissioned Officers, Petty Officers, and Military 
Construction Personnel Who Have Served the Designated Period of 
Military Service", dated Moscow, the Kremlin, 15 April 1994 and 
signed by Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin] 
  [Text] In accordance with the Russian Federation laws "On 
Defense" and "On Military Service Obligation and Military 
Service," I decree that: 
  1. A total of 216,000 citizens of the Russian Federation 
born between 1967 and 1976, including those who are studying in 
day departments of establishments of primary and secondary 
professional education and are not entitled to a deferment, are 
to be drafted in April-June 1994 for military service in the 
Russian Federation Armed Forces and in other forces and military 
formations. 
  2. Soldiers, seamen, noncommissioned officers, petty 
officers, and military construction personnel who have served 
the designated period of military service are to be discharged 
in April-June 1994. 
  3. The Russian Federation Government and organs of executive 
power in the republics, krays, oblasts, the cities of Moscow and 
St. Petersburg, the autonomous oblast, and autonomous okrugs are 
to ensure that measures are taken to draft citizens for military 
service. 
  4. The Russian Federation Ministry of Defense together with 
other ministries and departments where there is provision for 
military service are to submit for approval their proposals for 
the placement of citizens drafted for military service in 
April-June 1994. 
  5. Persons drafted for military service are to be 
transported as a rule in teams in the passenger cars of trains 
or in airplanes (ships) in accordance with a special schedule. 
  The Russian Federation Ministry of Railways and the Russian 
Federation Ministry of Transport are to set aside the necessary 
quantity of rolling stock and airplanes (ships) or places in 
passenger cars and planes (ships) in accordance with requests 
from the relevant command to transport the said persons at given 
times, with provision for security measures; payment for the 
transport is to be charged at the present mutually agreed 
tariffs. 
  6. This Edict comes into force from the moment of its 
signing. 
  [Signed] President of the Russian Federation B. Yeltsin 
  [Dated]Moscow, The Kremlin, 15 April 1994 
  No. 784 

</TEXT>

