<H3> <TI>   Grachev Order on Draft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Order on Draft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2004094394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2004094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Order No. 116 of the Russian Federation Minister of Defense </F>
"On the Drafting of Citizens of the Russian Federation for 
Military Service in April-June 1994, and the Transfer to the 
Reserve of Soldiers, Seamen, Noncommissioned Officers, Petty 
Officers, and Military Construction Personnel who Have Served 
the Designated Period of Military Service", dated Moscow, 15 
April 1994 and signed by Russian Federation Minister of Defense, 
Army General Pavel Grachev] 
  [Text] In execution of the Russian Federation president's 
Edict No. 784 of 15 April 1994, I order that: 
  1. Soldiers, seamen, noncommissioned officers, petty 
officers, and military construction personnel who have served 
the designated period of military service be transferred to the 
reserve from the ranks of the Russian Federation Armed Forces in 
April-June 1994. 
  2. Commanders of forces in military districts and military 
commissars ensure jointly with local administration heads the 
organization and implementation in April-June 1994 of the draft 
for military service in the Russian Federation Armed Forces and 
other forces and military units of citizens of the Russian 
Federation born between 1967 and 1976 who do not have the right 
to a deferment of and exemption from being drafted for military 
service. 
  3. The order be posted in all companies, batteries, 
squadrons, and on ships. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation Minister of Defense 
  Army General P. Grachev 

</TEXT>

