<H3> <TI>   Internal Troops Chief on Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Internal Troops Chief on Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2004073094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 20 Apr 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK2004073094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report under the "In Brief" rubric: "They Are </F>
Getting Ready for May Day"] 
  [Text] The Russian Federation internal troops "will be on 
duty on a reinforced basis; however, there will be no order to 
put them in full combat readiness" during the May Day 
celebrations, stated Colonel General Anatoliy Kulikov, internal 
troops commander, in a news briefing in Moscow yesterday. He 
pointed out that being on reinforced duty means reinforced 
security at a number of troop facilities to prevent seizures of 
weapons and hardware. "No concentration of forces from the 
other regions in Moscow is contemplated," the commander 
underlined. In his words, internal troops would be enlisted 
during the May Day celebrations to help the militia "as a 
reserve at the point of permanent deployment, as well as in 
separate regions in Moscow." 

</TEXT>

