  [Text] Belarusian Deputy Prime Minister Mikhail 
Myasnikovich believes that the Belarusian Supreme Soviet will 
certainly ratify the treaty with Russia on the unification of 
monetary systems. Speaking at a news conference at the third 
annual session of the Council of European Bank Managers, he said 
that Russian Central Bank Chairman Viktor Gerashchenko accepts 
the Belarusian approach toward a common emission policy within 
the framework of the unified monetary system. 

