<H3> <TI>   Industrialists To Support Kebich for President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Industrialists To Support Kebich for President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804202294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1804202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarus industrialists and entrepreneurs will 
support Vyacheslav Kebich, current head of republican 
government, in the forthcoming presidential elections. 
BELINFORM reports that this decision was adopted by the Belarus 
Confederation of Industrialists and Entrepreneurs at an 
extraordinary meeting. At the meeting, the confederation 
approved the government's activity aimed at creating a single 
economic space with Russia -- the treaty on merging Russia's and 
Belarus' monetary systems -- and proposed to submit it to a 
session of the republican Supreme Soviet for examination. 

</TEXT>

