<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] There are many rumors about Russia's position in the 
Yugoslav conflict. Specifically, today the Foreign Ministry 
denied a report on a possible severance of diplomatic relations 
between Moscow and Belgrade. 
  Yevgeniy Podkolzin, commander of Russian airborne landing 
troops, described as speculations reports on a withdrawal of the 
Russian battalion of Blue Helmets from Sarajevo. He said that 
this issue has not even been discussed. Also, a group of 
Russian servicemen was dispatched there yesterday, and today it 
was followed by another one. 
  Russian Blue Berets have been serving with UN peace-keeping 
forces in Yugoslavia for over two years. Two Russian battalions 
are stationed in the eastern sector and in Sarajevo area. Now 
their personnel is being relieved, which is a normal rotation. 
Two hundred paras are replacing their comrades in the hottest 
spot in the world. They have left for Yugoslavia from Ryazan. 

