<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia's Failure To Veto NATO Actions Criticized </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia's Failure To Veto NATO Actions Criticized </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2004085794 Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM2004085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Yevgeniy Popov article: "A `Blue Sword' for Harakiri?"] </F>
  [Excerpts] [Passage omitted] The NATO air strikes on the 
Serbian positions near Gorazde created an entirely new situation 
in the Bosnian war. The United States and the other Western 
countries, using the mandate of the UN peacemaking forces, have 
effectively entered the civil war on the Muslim side. The 
events of the past few days show that the danger of the 
internationalization and creeping proliferation of the military 
conflict in the Balkans is increasing constantly. [passage 
omitted] 
  The only way out of the Bosnian confrontation is peace 
talks, 
to which the Bosnian Serb leaders have long been urging the 
Muslims and their U.S. and NATO protectors. 
  The NATO order to bomb the Serbian positions was given 
immediately after a telephone conversation between U.S. 
Secretary of State Christopher and Russian Foreign Minister 
Kozyrev, who then immediately flew to Belgrade where he held 
talks that night with Serbian President Milosevic. 
  It does not seem, however, that even after that any 
fundamentally new emphasis appeared in Russian diplomacy's 
bipartite and ambiguous stance, which effectively encouraged the 
air attacks. Russia is continuing to refrain from using its 
right of veto to halt the aggression against the Serbs and 
achieve the lifting of what are essentially genocidal economic 
sanctions imposed on Yugoslavia. The appeal to urgently convene 
an extraordinary session of the Security Council has been left 
in midair. [passage omitted] 
  After the "slap in the face for Russia's prestige" (to use 
Sergey Shakhray's well-known emotional verdict), Moscow is 
apparently still ready to turn the other cheek for further 
encouragement for the United States and NATO in the same vein!.. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

