<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Praises Russian Role in Peace Process </H4>

<F P=102> LD1904162394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1500 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 19 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin received visiting Palestinian president and PLO leader 
Yasir 'Arafat here today to discuss the mideastern situation, 
the state and prospects for the Arab-Israeli settlement and ways 
to develop the Russian-Palestinian cooperation. 
  Comprehensive and just peace in the Middle East remains a 
Russian strategic priority in the region vitally important for 
Russia, said the president. 
  Boris Yeltsin is satisfied with the on-going 
Israeli-Palestinian negotiations to overcome confrontation and 
build a solid peace infrastructure despite all the difficulties. 
He reaffirmed the Russian firm intention as a co-sponsor of the 
mideastern peace process to render comprehensive assistance to 
further progress at Arab-Israeli negotiations. 
  In his turn, Yasir 'Arafat praised Russian contribution to 
the mideastern peace process and achievement of positive results 
in the Arab-Israeli dialogue. In his opinion, Russian 
diplomatic efforts has played a considerable role in settlement 
of difficulties resulting from the February tragedy in Hebron, 
as well as in the implementation of measures to consolidate 
Palestinian security in fulfilment of the U.N. Security 
Council's Resolution 904. 
  The PLO leader thanked Russia for its intention to help 
Palestinians in the organization of self-government in the Gaza 
Strip and the Jericho area. 
  The sides stressed their striving to consolidate historical 
relations between Russia and the Arab people of Palestine, the 
presidential press service reports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-16824 </DOCNO>
