<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Seeks Pressure on Israel </H4>

<F P=102> AU2004102094 Paris AFP in English 0957 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2004102094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Moscow, April 20 (AFP) -- PLO chief Yasir 'Arafat 
called here Wednesday [20 April] for Russian leaders to press 
Israel "not to waste time" in launching Palestinian self-rule 
when they meet Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin next week. 
  'Arafat, at the end of a two-day visit, said that continued 
"manoeuvering and marking time" by Israel in concluding the 
Israeli-PLO autonomy deal would only "give a chance to all 
extremist elements on both sides to undermine the peace process." 
  "The 13th of April, the final day to finalize the Israeli 
withdrawal from Gaza and Jericho passed and nothing concrete 
happened," he said during a press conference before his 
departure. 
  He added that Israel "must bear responsibility in all 
events" 
and accused Rabin of stalling the peace negotiations on purpose. 
  "Rabin is not in a hurry because he has received from 
America 
the price of peace: all kinds of armaments, state of the art, 
including 25 airplanes, the hugest and very sophisticated 
computers, a garantee for a 10-million-dollar credit, all kinds 
of financial, economic, political and diplomatic help," he said. 
  "This had been achieved before the implementation of the 
accord." 
  'Arafat called for Russia as a co-sponsor of the Middle East 
peace process along with the United States to press the Israeli 
prime minister, when he visits Moscow next week, "not to waste 
time." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

