<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on PLO Chairman 'Arafat's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Official Views 'Arafat-Yeltsin Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD2004082794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0750 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004082794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Arkadiy Sidoruk] </F>
  [Text] Washington April 20 TASS -- "We believe that Russia, 
as co-chairman of the Madrid process, is playing a most 
important role in the peace-making efforts in the Middle East 
and in the endeavours to settle the Palestinian problem fairly," 
ITAR-TASS was told by assistant director of the Palestinian 
centre in Washington Sa'id Hamid. "This explains the importance 
of the Moscow meeting between Chairman of the PLO Executive 
Committee Yasir 'Arafat and Russian President Boris Yeltsin," he 
added" 
  The Palestinian representative said the meeting was 
"exceptionally important". In his opinion, it was a logical 
continuation of the consistent efforts lately exerted by the 
Russian diplomacy in the Middle East. Moscow has always 
expressed concern over the situation in the region and has done 
its best to achieve stability there. 
  "We are thankful to Russia for its understanding of our 
concerns and anxieties, understanding of the legality of our 
rights for which we are striving. We are thankful to it for its 
good offices, which it is ready to offer us," Hamid stressed. 
He expressed the hope that the Russian president would use his 
influence to convince Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin during the 
latter's forthcoming trip to Moscow that Israel should fulfil 
the terms of the agreement on the settlement principles, signed 
by the PLO and Israel in Washington last September. "The 
principle of Palestinian self-government will remain a dead 
letter as long as the Israeli troops remain on the occupied 
territories," Hamid stated. 

</TEXT>

