<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Invites Latvian President To Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Invites Latvian President To Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904154194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1328 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Latvian President Guntis Ulmanis has received an 
invitation from Russian president Yeltsin to arrive in Moscow on 
April 21 for a working visit. 
  He said that President Yeltsin had expressed a desire that 
the two sides sign a package of agreements on conditions for the 
Russian troop pull-out, which was initialed on March 15. 
  Interfax was told by a spokesman for the Latvian president 
that Ulmanis promised to give a reply on Tuesday night. 
  The spokesman said that speaking with an ambassador Ulmanis 
had said that on April 20 the Latvian parliament will take a 
decision on the possibility of the signing of the package of 
agreements. He said, however, that despite parliament's 
decision the meeting between the Russian and Latvian presidents 
would be expedient. 
  President Ulmanis said that there are problems in the 
Russian-Latvian relations which should be clarified, including 
in relation to the Russian president's decision of April 5 which 
provides for the creation of a military base in Latvia. The 
emergence of the document caused a wave of criticisms in the 
Baltic countries and the Ulmanis said that his visit to Moscow, 
earlier planned for April 20, would be postponed for an 
indefinite period. 
prepared by the president's administration, if that is indeed 
the case." 

</TEXT>

