<H3> <TI>   `Serious Concern' Expressed Over Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Serious Concern' Expressed Over Nagorno-Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904152594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1433 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904152594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow April 19 TASS -- The renewed escalation of 
bloodshed around Nagorno-Karabakh is causing serious concern, 
deputy chief of the Russian Foreign Ministry Department of 
Information and Press Mikhail Demurin said at a briefing today. 
  According to the official, the Russian Foreign Ministry, 
acting as a mediator, rejects attempts made by the conflicting 
sides, in the given case the Armenians of Nagorno-Karabakh, to 
extend and consolidify [as received] their positions when the 
situation has long since taken a turn towards peace. 
  Recent attacks in the north of Nagorno-Karabakh are being 
negatively reflected on the prospects of negotiations, Mikhail 
Demurin noted. 

</TEXT>

