<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Albania Develops `New Principles' in Russian Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Albania Develops `New Principles' in Russian Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004105494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1025 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Valeriy Sevryukov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS -- "Relations between Albania 
and Russia are being developed on the new principles of 
partnership, cooperation and mutual advantage. They take into 
account the specific features of the Russian Federation as 
successor of the former USSR, as a state with a huge economic 
and intellectual potential, as permanent member of the U.N. 
Security Council," Albanian Ambassador to the Russian Federation 
Arbet Cici told ITAR-TASS. 
  These are the principles," he said, "on which Albania bases 
its relations with other states in the interests of the region. 
They rule out political and ideological servility, which had 
sometimes existed in the past". 
  "During the past three years," the diplomat noted, "the new 
Albanian-Russian relations were backed up by a consular 
agreement on mutual trips, by agreements on air traffic and 
automobile service, on public health and the environment, as 
well as other inter-departmental agreements in the sphere of 
education, culture, and the arts. 
  Agreements on the protection of investments, avoidance of 
double taxation, cooperation in the sphere of education, 
culture, science and technology, as well as a consular 
convention and several other documents are ready to be signed. 
  "The laid beginning appears to be promising and is expected 
to open up promising vistas for cooperation between our two 
countries," the ambassador said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

