<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chairman of the State Duma Committee for 
international affairs Vladimir Lukin considers "improbable" that 
the lower chamber of parliament will hold a closed meeting to 
discuss the situation in former Yugoslavia Wednesday, April 20. 
Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy Churkin earlier 
reported to Interfax about the possibility of holding such a 
meeting after meeting with speaker of the State Duma Ivan Rybkin. 
  According to Lukin, the Council of the State Duma on Tuesday 
decided to put on the agenda of the plenary meeting on Wednesday 
