<H3> <TI>   Supreme Council Elects Kekilbayev New Chairman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supreme Council Elects Kekilbayev New Chairman </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004092394 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 0800 GMT 
20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004092394 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As has already been reported, five candidates were 
nominated for the post of speaker yesterday: Abish Kekilbayev, 
Gaziz Aldamzharov, Sultan Sartayev, Olzhas Suleymenov, and 
Kuanysh Sultanov. At the afternoon session Suleymenov withdrew 
his candidature. Today after voting, two candidates had the 
majority of votes: Abish Kekilbayev and Gaziz Aldamzharov. 
Ninety-two deputies voted for and 84 against Abish Kekilbayev; 
and 62 for and 107 against Gaziz Aldamzharov. 
  So, Abish Kekilbayev was elected chairman of the Supreme 
Kenges of the Republic of Kazakhstan. 

</TEXT>

