<H3> <TI>   First Round of Government-Opposition Talks Success </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    First Round of Government-Opposition Talks Success </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904171294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1603 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris </F>
Krivoshey and Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow 19 April TASS -- The first round of 
inter-Tajik negotiations has reached its major goal of the 
beginning of a political dialogue between the Tajik Government 
and the opposition. The negotiations were held under the U.N. 
aegis and with active participation of the Russian Federation, 
special envoy of the United Nations Secretary-General Ramiro 
Piriz-Ballon told a news conference here today. 
  In his words, the Tajik Government and the opposition are 
determined to find a peaceful solution to the complicated 
political problems in order to achieve national reconciliation 
in Tajikistan and restore national economy. 
  The sides have managed to agree on the agenda and sign an 
appeal on all sides to abstain from actions that may endanger 
the results of political negotiations. 
  It was an important discussion, but the sides understood it 
is impossible to achieve a comprehensive decision at the first 
round of negotiations. They will be continued in other places. 
Iran and Pakistan have offered their territories for further 
inter-Tajik talks, said Ramiro Piriz-Ballon. 

</TEXT>

