<H3> <TI>   International Groups To Examine New Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International Groups To Examine New Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904194094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1812 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by KHOVAR news agency correspondent Valeriy Zhukov </F>
for TASS] 
  [Text] Dushanbe 19 April TASS -- A draft new Tajik 
constitution circulated here today by the KHOVAR news agency 
proclaims Tajikistan a sovereign, democratic, law-governed, 
secular and integral republic. 
  The Majelis Milli (National Assembly -- parliament) is the 
supreme representative and legislative body of the Republic, and 
the president elected on the basis of universal, equal and 
direct electoral right in secret voting for a five-year term is 
the head of state and the executive power. 
  The text of the document will be sent to specialized 
international organizations for an examination. 

</TEXT>

