<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Premier Holds News Conference on Economic Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Premier Holds News Conference on Economic Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904115094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1010 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By KHOVAR agency correspondent Negmat Ochilov for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe April 19 TASS -- "Tajikistan strives for a 
new political and economic system and plans to conduct an 
open-door policy to pull out of the dire crisis," Tajik Premier 
Abdulmadjid Samadov told a news conference in Dushanbe on 
Tuesday. 
  Replying to journalists, he said that the republic "firmly 
abides by the position of pooling the monetary systems of 
Tajikistan and Russia". This notwithstanding, bank notes with 
national symbols will appear in the republic in May. 
  According to the premier, they are called upon to serve the 
needs of the domestic market. This measure is temporary, 
Samadov stressed, and the reason for it is "that Tajikistan is 
now at an intermediary stage of pooling the monetary systems of 
the two states". 
  The meeting with journalists was arranged in connection with 
the opening of a national strategic research centre which is 
called upon to prepare true information on the situation in 
various spheres and to carry out examination of the most 
important decisions taken by the republican leadership. 
  The centre is also instructed to work out the government's 
position on major economic projects. 

</TEXT>

