<H3> <TI>   Niyazov Rejects Church Intevention in State Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Niyazov Rejects Church Intevention in State Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904205494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2001 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904205494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Glazovskaya] </F>
  [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat] 19 April TASS -- "Any attempts 
to intervene in state affairs will be decisively stopped," said 
President Saparmurad Niyazov during a meeting with religious 
workers of Turkemnistan today. He also emphasised that 
Turkmenistan is a "secular democratic state laws of which give 
everbody right to freedom of religion." 
  The head of the Turkmen state called on religious workers to 
help maintain in the future civic peace and social concord in 
the country which is the most important condition for fulfilling 
the nationwide program of "10 years of prosperity." Niyazov 
also appealed to use the church's authority for waging war 
against drug addiction, an evil which is beginning to corrupt 
the youth. 
  Saparmurad Niyazov announced the creation of a council of 
religious affairs under the president of Turkmenistan which will 
consist of Moslem Qazis together with workers of the Russian 
Orthodox Church. 
  According to an announcement, the national festival Kurban 
Bairam (Id) will be celebrated in Turkmenistan for three days 
from 20 to 22 May. 

</TEXT>

