<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry `Condemns' Serb Actions in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry `Condemns' Serb Actions in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1904182694 Tallinn Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press 
Release in English 0833 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1904182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Ministry of Foreign Affairs Press 
Release </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Immediate release" from the Estonian Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs in Tallinn on 19 April: "Statement in Connection With 
the Situation in Bosnia" -- received via Internet E-LIST] 
  [Text] The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Estonia 
expresses its concern in connection with the increased military 
activity in Bosnia. The Foreign Ministry condemns the actions 
of the Serbian armed forces in Bosnia, which are aimed against 
the United Nations peacekeeping forces and against the "safe 
areas" declared by the UN Security Council. By ignoring 
decisions of the UN Security Council and earlier cease-fire 
agreements, the Serbs in Bosnia set themselves against the 
international community. 
  The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Estonia greatly 
respects the UN decision to create "safe areas" and expresses 
its dissatisfaction over the fact that agreements achieved 
during the peace process are not being lived up to. This is one 
more indication that the world organization must take even more 
decisive steps to prevent the spread of the conflict and to 
achieve a general cease-fire in Bosnia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

