<H3> <TI>   Acting Chief of Defense Forces Central Staff Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Acting Chief of Defense Forces Central Staff Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1904162794 Tallinn BNS in English 1500 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1904162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Apr 18, BNS -- Ltn. Col. Arvo Sirel took 
over as acting chief of staff the leadership of the Estonian 
defense forces' Central Staff from Col. Ants Laaneots today. 
  Laaneots, who entered his resignation on March 24, was 
listed 
into reserve as of today. Laaneots' resignation was approved by 
the country's commander in chief, Maj. Gen. Aleksander Einseln, 
on March 31. 
  The new acting chief of staff, Sirel, earlier occupied the 
position of head of the Central Staff's operative department. 
  He was now replaced on the post by Ltn. Col. Jaan Poldma. 
  A spokesman at the Central Staff said Laaneots has not 
revealed so far what he would do after resignation. According 
to information obtained by BNS, he has been offered the 
opportunity to continue his education in Western military 
academies, as well as a position with the Defense Ministry. 

</TEXT>

