<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Heavy Fighting Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Heavy Fighting Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904121594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1036 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There was heavy fighting between Armenia and 
Azerbaijan in the Azerbaijani parts of Nagorno-Karabakh in the 
north and northeast over the past twenty four hours, the press 
center for the enclave told Interfax. 
  Karabakh units on Monday beat off the Azerbaijani advance to 
the east of the administrative center Mardakert regaining 
strategic points outside Lenivan. 
  The center put Azerbaijani losses at more than 80 troops, 
one 
tank and one APC [armored personnel carrier]. Five Armenians 
were also killed and 17 others injured. One Armenian APC was 
destroyed. 
  There was no fighting overnight with positional battles 
being 
reported by 11:00 on Tuesday. 
  For its part, the defence ministry in Baku reports about a 
further Armenian advance in Ter-Ter and Geranboy regions of 
Azerbaijan north of the disputed territory. Armenian forces 
lost two tanks and one APC after last night's fighting there, 
according to Baku. One Armenian tank and one APC were also hit 
during battles in Agdam region. 
  The ministry said that dozens of Armenian soldiers were 
killed or wounded. 

</TEXT>

