<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ulmanis Invited to Moscow </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ulmanis Invited to Moscow </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904105194 Riga Radio Riga Network in Latvian 1000 GMT 19 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Riga Radio Riga Network </F>
<F P=105>  Latvian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At the invitation of State President Guntis Ulmanis, 
Aleksandr Rannikh, Russian ambassador extraordinary and 
plenipotentiary to Latvia, today met the Latvian president. The 
ambassador orally conveyed Russian President Yeltsin's 
invitation for the Latvian president to pay a working visit to 
Moscow on 21 April and to sign earlier initialled agreements. 
  Our president expressed his thanks for the invitation, 
explaining that he considers such a visit to be useful because 
there are many issues concerning Latvian-Russian relations which 
need to be clarified, especially those related to the order of 5 
April. 
  Talks with Boris Yeltsin at which an exchange of opinions 
and 
coordination of views concerning the initialled agreements and 
the prospects for future relations between Latvia and Russia 
would have great significance on the international scale. 
  The Latvian president recalled that the Saeima will discuss 
the possibility of signing the agreements at tomorrow's 
extraordinary plenary session. 
  The situation in the countries of the former USSR and the 
latest events on the territory of former Yugoslavia may also be 
discussed at the talks with the Russian president. 
  A reply from the Latvian state president on his possible 
visit to Moscow will be given to the Russian ambassador later 
today. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

