<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Parliament Speaker Meets U.S. Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Parliament Speaker Meets U.S. Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1904162294 Tallinn BNS in English 2100 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1904162294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Apr 18, BNS -- Latvian Saeima (parliament) 
Deputy Speaker Andrejs Krastins met on Monday [18 April] with 
U.S. State Department's political experts Julie Cohen, Martin 
Schwartz and U.S. Embassy in Latvia Secretary Scott Dean. 
  The group discussed relations between Latvia and Russia and 
problems related to Latvia's draft citizenship law. 
  Krastins also pointed to shortcomings in the initialed 
Latvian- Russian agreements on troop withdrawal. 
  The package fails to demand compensation for Russian damages 
to Latvia, allows Russian forces to retain ownership rights on 
real estate and tolerates foundation of Latvian-Russian joint 
ventures on the basis of former military installations, said 
Krastins. 
  Krastins reiterated that Latvia is interested to receive 
international guarantees for the process of the signature of the 
troop withdrawal package and the control of its implementation. 
  Dean voiced his country's support for the conclusion of an 
interstate agreement that would fully resolve the issue of 
Russian troop withdrawal from Latvia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

