<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tskhinvali, 18 Apr -- The headquarters of the 
peacekeeping forces deployed in Tskhinvali told an Iberia 
correspondent that, today a session of the so-called South 
Ossetian Supreme Council was held. Following the elections, 
communists obtained 24 seats out of a total of 34, the National 
Unity Party got 6 seats, and 4 seats went to representatives of 
various public organizations. 
  Ludwig Chibirov was today elected chairman to the state 
Nikhas [South Ossetia's parliament]. 

