<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Emergency UN Session on Gorazde Sought </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Emergency UN Session on Gorazde Sought </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904154594 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1500 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904154594 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pakistan has appealed for an emergency session of 
the UN Security Council [UNSC] to consider the situation as a 
result of the Serb attack on the besieged Muslim town of Gorazde 
in Bosnia. An official press statement issued in Islamabad says 
that, through Pakistani efforts, a group of nonaligned countries 
have presented a draft resolution in the UN Security Council 
demanding the withdrawal of Serb forces from Gorazde. The draft 
resolution calls upon the UN protection force to use all 
available means, including the use of force, to foil the Serb 
aggression against Gorazde. Pakistan hopes that the members of 
the UN Security Council will discharge their obligation to save 
the people of Goradze from the aggression. They should take 
urgent and concrete steps for the security of the population of 
Gorazde and other UN-protected areas. Pakistan has especially 
appealed to the North Atlantic Council [three preceding words in 
English] to immediately order air action against the Serbs. The 
statement says the government and people of Pakistan are deeply 
anguished by the brutal action and aggression by Serb forces 
against the Muslims of Gorazde. 

</TEXT>

