<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commander Views Situation in N. Ossetia, Ingushetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commander Views Situation in N. Ossetia, Ingushetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904203794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1526 
GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904203794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 19 Apr -- The fact that the leaders of North 
Ossetia and Ingushetia have sat down at the conference table is 
no small contribution of the Russian interior troops who are 
carrying out peacekeeping functions in the region, their 
commander, Colonel General Anatoliy Kulikov believes. He was 
meeting Russian and foreign journalists at a briefing at the 
Russian Internal Affairs Ministry today. 
  Kulikov noted that the presence of the interior troops in 
the 
emergency situation zone has not only stabilized but also, to a 
considerable extent, improved the crime situation. The number 
of people who have been killed in North Ossetia and Ingushetia 
is substantially fewer than in neighboring republics and oblasts 
with the same population, and the crime level is an average of 
20 percent less. 
  Describing the activities of the troops in the hot spot, 
General Kulikov cited the following figures: Last year troop 
details confiscated over 600 fire arms, about 30,000 pieces of 
ammunition, hundreds of grenades and explosives, 16 artillery 
systems and grenade-throwers, and nine armored vehicles. This 
year seven special operations to disarm illegal formations have 
been carried out. The troops' catch includes 62 firearms, over 
240 grenades, mines, and explosive devices, and over 20 kg of 
explosive substances. 
  In the time the troops have been in the emergency situation 
zone over 100 special operations have been carried out in which 
not a single local inhabitant has been killed, Kulikov stressed. 
  Unfortunately, he went on, the servicemen are constantly 
risking their lives in fulfilling combat and service tasks in 
the region. Last year, the temporary quarters of units and 
sub-units and also troop details were subjected to shelling and 
armed attacks on 126 occasions, as a result of which seven 
people were killed and 133 wounded. This year there have 
already been over 20 attacks and shellings. There have been no 
losses among the men of the interior troops. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-16891 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov076_d_94004" </HT>


