<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   South Ossetians Protest Border Post With North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    South Ossetians Protest Border Post With North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904170094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1328 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904170094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Some of the South Ossetian citizens have taken the 
plans to equip a border post on the Russian-Georgian border as 
an attempt to divide the peoples of North and South Ossetia. 
According to Interfax sources, about 300 citizens of South 
Ossetia (Georgia) have arrived in Vladikavkaz, the capital of 
North Ossetia (Russia) to organize a meeting in front of the 
parliament building. 
  The republic leaders persuaded the demonstrators to move to 
the Art Center and meet with North Ossetian President Akhsarbek 
Galazov. The president said that the most important thing now 
was "to work in order to turn Ossetia into an economically 
mighty country." 
  He also said that the North Ossetian leaders would make 
efforts to ensure that the Russian-Georgian border between South 
and North Ossetia be transparent and never divide the peoples. 

</TEXT>

