<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karachayevo-Cherkessian Parliament Restructured </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karachayevo-Cherkessian Parliament Restructured </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004103194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0908 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004103194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Nikolay Styazhkin] </F>
  [Text] Cherkessk April 20 TASS -- The Supreme Soviet of the 
Karachayevo-Cherkessian Republic has been transformed into the 
People's Assembly. All the functions and powers of the 
representative authority will be transferred to it. This 
decision was taken by the session of the Republic's Supreme 
Soviet held in Cherkessk on Tuesday. Viktor Savelyev, president 
of the Republic's Supreme Soviet, was endorsed as speaker of the 
National Assembly. 
  The Presidium of the Republican Supreme Soviet has been 
dissolved. The Nationalities Council of the People's Assembly 
has been formed. It includes five deputies from each of the 
native peoples inhabitting Karachayevo-Cherkessia -- Abaz, 
Karachay, Nogay, Russians, Cherkessians, and two deputies 
representing other peoples living in Karachayevo-Cherkessia. 
  The speaker of the People's Assembly will be chairman of the 
Nationalities Council. The draft constitution of Karachayevo- 
Cherkessia is to be worked out by the Council by July 1. After 
being considered by the National Assembly it will be put to a 
natiowide referendum. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

