  [Text] ITAR-TASS has circulated President Yeltsin's 
directive on an investigation of whether laws and other legal 
enactments adopted in the Republic of Mordovia conform with the 
Russian Constitution. To this end, the document envisages the 
establishment of a special commission made up of representatives 
of the Russian Justice Ministry, the president's State Legal 
Administration, and the president's Administration for Work with 
Territories. Sergey Filatov, head of the president's 
administration, has been given a week to endorse the composition 
of this commission. 

