<H3> <TI>   Perm Oblast Coal Strike Averted at Last Minute </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Perm Oblast Coal Strike Averted at Last Minute </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1904143794 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 19 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1904143794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Aleksandr Lebedinskiy report: "It Is Harder To Receive </F>
Than to Work"] 
  [Text] Perm Oblast -- An open-ended strike by the miners 
of Kizelovskiy Coalfield in Perm Oblast was to have started 
yesterday. The reason was purely economic -- the nonpayment of 
wages since the beginning of the year. But if their labor is 
not paid for within a week, the miners warned, demands will be 
made that the government should resign and presidential 
elections be held ahead of schedule. 
  The countdown was about to begin, but news spread of 2.7 
billion rubles arriving on time; this should be enough to settle 
accounts with the miners. But only for January. It was decided 
to postpone the strike. Evidently, until this money runs out. 

</TEXT>

