<H3> <TI>   Two Major Novosibirsk Banks Fail </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Two Major Novosibirsk Banks Fail </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1904151494 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM1904151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Aleksandr Chernykh report: "Novosibirsk Bank Failures"] </F>
  [Text] Novosibirsk -- Two major Novosibirsk banks have 
announced that they are ending operations and proposing that 
clients close their accounts. 
  The first bank to fail -- the "Siberian Development Bank" -- 
has been on its last legs for more than a year. This led to a 
change of management and the attraction of considerable amounts 
of funds to rescue the situation. It did not help. Experts 
believe that the collapse was inevitable. The Novosibirsk 
management of "Mosbiznesbank" lent a hand to their bankrupt 
colleagues. But, naturally, not in the form of money. They 
offered staff from the failed bank jobs at their new branch. 
  The second victim of competition and market conditions has 
been the "Novosibirsk Innovation Commercial Bank." 

</TEXT>

