<H3> <TI>   Further on Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904202294 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1945 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- On 19 April Ukraine President Leonid 
Kravchuk attended the opening of a new outpatient child clinic 
in Kharkovskiy district intended for 30,000 local children. 
  The Ukrainian president was interviewed on current political 
issues. He said, in particular, that the Black Sea Fleet 
problem must be resolved as soon as possible. "We need to settle 
it as soon as possible, so that instead of a Russian fleet with 
Russia's laws, Ukraine will have its own fleet. I do not see 
any other option than leasing the Sevastopol base to the Russian 
fleet. Leaving the Ukrainian Navy there would be dangerous. 
There will be no peace as long as the Ukrainian and Russian 
naval forces are together." 
  Asked about his nomination in the next presidential election 
by a group of electors in Vinnitsa oblast, Leonid Kravchuk 
replied: "I am grateful to the voters. I have very close ties 
with Vinnitsa oblast; I was nominated and elected to parliament 
in Yampolskiy constituency there, and when I was nominated for 
presidency they also supported me, so I am sincerely grateful." 

</TEXT>

