<H3> <TI>   Naval Delegation Visits U.S.; To Observe Exercises </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Naval Delegation Visits U.S.; To Observe Exercises </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1904194794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1900 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1904194794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of Ukrainian naval servicemen, headed 
by Rear Admiral Mykola Kostrov, deputy commander in chief of 
Ukraine's Navy, is currently visiting the United States. The 
press center of the Ukrainian Navy reports in connection with 
this that during their trip, members of the delegation will 
visit military education facilities, educational centers, and 
U.S. Marine training grounds. Ukrainian officers have been 
offered the possibility to observe a joint training exercise of 
U.S. Navy personnel and Marines on the Atlantic coast. All 
expenses connected with the delegation's trip are being covered 
by the U.S. side. 

</TEXT>

