<H3> <TI>   Romania Accused of Interference in Moldovan Affairs </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romania Accused of Interference in Moldovan Affairs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904193194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1856 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Demidetskiy] </F>
  [Text] Kishinev [Chisinau] 19 April TASS -- A statement of 
the Romanian Parliament's Chamber of Deputies to denounce 
Moldovan joining of the Commonwealth of Independent States and 
the CIS economic union was estimated by Kishinev as an 
interference in internal affairs of independent Moldova. 
  Deputy Moldovan parliament speaker and leader of the ruling 
Agrarian-Democratic Party Dumitru Motspan told ITAR-TASS that 
the leadership of independent Moldova "does not intend to ask 
for permission to conclude beneficial treaties and will not 
tolerate interference in its internal affairs." 

</TEXT>

