<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Urges Serbs To Withdraw From Gorazde </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Urges Serbs To Withdraw From Gorazde </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904171994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1705 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 19 TASS -- The international communist 
[as received] must do its best to achieve a political settlement 
of the Bosnian crisis, says a statement of Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin circulated here today by his press service. 
  "The conflict in Bosnia and Herzegovina is on the verge of 
dangerous escalation despite active diplomatic efforts of Russia 
taken together with the United Nations and other members of the 
international community," says the document. 
  "The Bosnian Serb leadership must fulfill its promises given 
to Russia, stop the attacks and withdraw from Gorazde announced 
by the United Nations a `safety zone', enable the introduction 
of U.N. forces in the area and unblock the U.N. personnel in 
Bosnia and Herzegovina." 
  The Russian president "confirmed the proposal to hold a 
summit meeting with participation of Russia, the United States 
and the European Union and in the presence of U.N. 
representatives". 
  "No doubt, such a meeting must be thoroughly prepared. 
Corresponding instructions have been given to the Russian 
Foreign Ministry," says the statement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

