<H3> <TI>   Rakhmonov, Yeltsin Hold Talks During CIS Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rakhmonov, Yeltsin Hold Talks During CIS Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904112094 Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network in Russian 
0400 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1904112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] During the intervals of the sessions of the CIS 
council of the heads of states and governments in Moscow, 
Emomali Rakhmonov, chairman of the Supreme Soviet of the 
Republic of Tajikistan, held talks with Russian Federation 
President Boris Yeltsin. 
  In a meeting which was held in an atmosphere of mutual 
understanding they discussed strengthening and expanding 
mutually beneficial cooperation between Tajikistan and Russia. 
  In addition, Emomali Rakhmonov held talks with Viktor 
Chernomyrdin, chairman of the Council of Ministers of the 
Russian Federation; Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of the Russian 
Federation Council; Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev; and 
Islam Karimov, president of the Republic of Uzbekistan. 

