<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Press Secretary Urges Signing Peace Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Secretary Urges Signing Peace Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904140294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1011 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1904140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, April 18 (SNARK)--Armenian President's 
Acting Press Secretary Levon Zurabyan declares that through 
Azerbaijan's fault the chance to achieve the guaranteed 
armistice was lost though such chance existed at the Moscow 
meeting of the CIS members' leaders. 
  Speaking at today's briefing he also mentioned that 
Azerbaijan's signing the Russian-sponsored agreement will bring 
to profits for all the sides: Armenia will be deblockaded, 
Nagorno-Karabakh will get all the security guarantees, 
Azerbaijan will get the territories. 
  Zurabyan also mentioned that the participants of the Moscow 
summit will supply Russia with the CIS mandate to realize its 
peacekeeping initiatives in Karabakh. 
  Answering the SNARK's question on Karabakh participation in 
signing the agreement, Levon Zurabyan said if Azerbaijan 
expresses its readiness to sign the agreement the Karabakh 
representatives' participation will be ensured. 

</TEXT>

