<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Reports Major Armenian Offensive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Reports Major Armenian Offensive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904124194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1036 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azeri President Heydar Aliyev has reported that the 
Armenian offensive in the zone of the Karabakh conflict that was 
launched right after the CIS summit ended in Moscow, "is the 
strongest one over the past period." 
  Addressing a conference in Baku with the government members 
and heads of the local administration, the president said that 
the "force and the character of the Armenian military operations 
indicate that the Armenians get military support from the 
outside." "Their military operations are being prepared by 
professional military experts," said Aliyev. 
  He said that the Azeri army rebuffs the aggressor. 
Azerbaijan has only one way out -- to defend itself and 
strengthen the country's defense potential. 
  He ordered that military commissariat to recruit additional 
soldiers within 10 days. Aliyev said that by his decree he 
dismissed three leaders of local military departments. The 
president ordered that the defense minister demote these chiefs 
and send them to fight on the frontline. 
  The president said that from now on the branches of the 
"power" ministries in the regions should be subordinate to the 
heads of the local administration. He said this was being done 
to improve the interaction between the representatives of the 
administrative-states local bodies. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

