<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   North Caucasian-Abkhazi Meeting `Postponed' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    North Caucasian-Abkhazi Meeting `Postponed' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904125094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1106 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Initially scheduled for Thursday [21 April] in 
Krasnodar, a meeting of North Caucasian and Abkhazi leaders has 
been postponed indefinitely. As Interfax has learned from the 
Krasnodar- based organizing committee, the meeting was put off 
because of the Russian Foreign Ministry's insistence on getting 
the Georgian leadership's consent for such an assembly first. 
  Meanwhile, as an Interfax correspondent reports, at a 
conference in Krasnodar on April 16-17, the working groups of 
experts drafted for the upcoming meeting a political statement 
on the mechanism for the functioning of peacekeepers in Abkhazia. 

</TEXT>

