<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Presidendial Candidates Registered for Election </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Presidendial Candidates Registered for Election </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1904112294 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1930 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1904112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the central electoral commission, not a 
single candidate has been registered in Kiev a week before the 
final date for registration of contenders for candidate for 
president of Ukraine. 
  Ivan Hulchenko, head of the section for working with 
parties, 
has informed UNIAN that as of 18 April the Central Electoral 
Commission (TsVK) had registered the Socialist and 
Social-Democratic parties of Ukraine as intending to nominate a 
contender for candidate for president of Ukraine. Apart from 
them another four parties (Communist Party of Ukraine, Labor 
Congress of Ukraine, Party of Free Peasants of Ukraine, and the 
"State Independence of Ukraine" association) have submitted 
registration documents. According to Ivan Hulchenko, they have 
to submit certain information, after which they will receive 
forms to collect 100,000 signatures in support of their 
contenders. 
  According to Stepan Hamanyuk, an employee at the 
registration 
section of the Central Electoral Commission, to date, a week 
before the final date for registration, the Central Electoral 
Commission has not registered a single contender for candidate 
for president of Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

