<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Newspaper Publishes Romanian Parliament Statement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Newspaper Publishes Romanian Parliament Statement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004161294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1101 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In adopting the decision to join the CIS, the 
Chisinau parliament reconfirmed the criminal Molotov-Ribbentrop 
pact and annulled the essential right of the Romanian nation for 
the integrity of its historic and spiritual territory, says the 
statement of the chamber of the Romanian parliament's deputies 
published by the newspaper Tsara, an organ of the Christian 
Democratic Popular Front of Moldova. 
  The statement points out that in 1812 and 1940 Bessarabia 
was 
torn from its homeland by means of agreements between various 
powers and despite the will of the Romanian people. 
  "The events which took place in 1989 and later made us 
hopeful that Bessarabia would be re-unified with its 
motherland," asserted the Romanian parliamentarians and said 
that the USSR Supreme Soviet had called the Molotov-Ribbentrop 
pact "which tore Bessarabia from Romania in 1940" invalid. 
  The chamber also gave its backing to Moldova's efforts to be 
integrated into European structures and "condemns actions of 
political forces trying to again include Moldova into the 
previous structures." 

</TEXT>

