<H3> <TI>   Says No `Concessions' To Be Made </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says No `Concessions' To Be Made </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104074094 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
0700 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Voziyanov; from the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Talks between Russian and Ukrainian military 
delegations on a stage-by-stage settlement of Black Sea Fleet 
problems begin in Sevastopol today. 
  Pavel Grachev, the head of the Russian delegation and 
Russian 
defense minister, said the Russian military delegation would not 
grant any favors or concessions going beyond the framework of 
the agreement and also the Massandra protocol and other 
documents concerning the fleet. 
  Pavel Grachev stressed the Russian delegation would approach 
the destiny of the Black Sea Fleet in a constructive and 
equitable manner. According to INTERFAX, the defense minister's 
view is that Russia has enough strength and resources to 
purchase the whole of the Black Sea Fleet altogether. 

</TEXT>

