<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meets Sevastopol Sailors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets Sevastopol Sailors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104094294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev, who is in 
Sevastopol for talks on dividing up the Black Sea Fleet, has had 
a meeting with personnel of the fleet. He said at the meeting 
that the Russian delegation will insist on separate bases for 
the Russian Black Sea Fleet and the Ukrainian Navy, and that the 
Russian Navy's base will remain in Sevastopol. The Russian 
minister called on the Black Sea sailors not to give in to 
provocations, but to show restraint and calm. 
  Our correspondent Yuriy Novikov reports that this afternoon 
there will be talks between the Russian and Ukrainian 
delegations on the fate of the Black Sea Fleet. It has been 
learned that the Ukrainian sidle is ready to hand over to Russia 
only some of the moorings and bases of the fleet in Sevastopol. 
The Russian delegation does not agree with this proposal and 
will insist on Russia being handed over all the fleet's bases in 
Sevastopol. 

</TEXT>

