<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karpenka Presents Platform, Rejects Money Merger </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karpenka Presents Platform, Rejects Money Merger </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104093894 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0700 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2104093894 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] My slogan in the presidential election campaign 
will be: Social accord and unity of all the people residing on 
Belarusian territory. This was said by Genadz Karpenka, 
candidate for the post of the first Belarusian president, at a 
news conference held on 19 April. Among the primary problems 
Karpenka singled out that will have to be resolved if he were to 
be elected were housing construction, the transformation of 
plants and factories into joint-stock enterprises, and the 
development of economic ties with all the CIS states including 
our close neighbors. For the first time ever, the candidate 
presented his viewpoint on the agricultural sector. He spoke 
skeptically about the treaty on unification of the monetary 
systems of Belarus and Russia. In his opinion, the current 
quite difficult situation should be resolved by economic 
measures, rather than by joining the ruble zone. Karpenka added 
that the main task is to make plants work, while money is only a 
by-product. 

</TEXT>

