<F P=102> LD2104062894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0615 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104062894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat] 21 April ITAR-TASS -- Chinese 
Premier Li Peng today continues his official visit to 
Turkmenistan. 
  On the eve of his arrival, the local press published a 
series 
of statements on relations between Turkmenistan and China by 
President Saparmurad Niyazov. Niyazov described these relations 
as having great perspectives. 
  "China is a great country, and its role in the Asian-Pacific 
region and the entire world is considerable," Turkmenistan's 
president said. 
  "We have no intention of copying somebody's model 
uncritically," Turkmenistan's leader said. "Along with this we 
are studying carefully and interestedly China's economic reform 
experience." 
  The head of the Chinese Government is on a 12-day tour of 
the 
Central Asian countries, including Turkmenistan, Kyrgyzstan, 
Kazakhstan and Mongolia. These visits were planned in spring of 
last year but had to be postponed because of the premier's 
unexpected illness. 

