<H4>    Starts Talks With Li Peng </H4>

<F P=102> LD2104080494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0735 
GMT 21 Apr 93 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104080494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Lyudmila Glazovskaya] </F>
  [Text] Ashkhabad [Ashgabat], 21 Apr -- Turkmen-Chinese 
summit talks started in Ashkhabad today. Turkmen President 
Saparmurad Niyazov and Li Peng, premier of the PRC State 
Council, have started discussing specific issues relating to the 
development of economic cooperation. 
  Journalists were allowed to be present only for the first 
few 
minutes of the meeting. However, these first few minutes did 
reveal that the meeting was exclusively about business. An 
understanding has virtually been reached on the purchase of 
Turkmen cotton by China. 
  Alongside the official talks, discussion is under way of 
draft intergovernmental agreements. These center on matters 
relating to projects for sending Turkmen gas to China and a 
number of other commercial and economic cooperation issues. 

</TEXT>

