<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaders Support Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Leaders Support Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004150094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1433 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS -- The leaders of Russian 
regions who met with President Boris Yeltsin to sum up the 
results of local elections adopted the following statement in 
Moscow on Wednesday. 
  "We, representatives of Russian regions, support the idea of 
signing the memorandum on civil peace and accord in Russia. 
  "We are confident that the implementation of the tasks set 
by 
this memorandum -- to ensure political stability, exclude any 
forms of extremism from the arsenal of methods used in political 
practice, set up lasting mechanisms of accord, establish a new 
political culture, overcome the estrangement between the society 
and power and, consequently, create favourable social atmosphere 
for successful continuation of reforms -- meet the inspirations 
of the overwhelming majority of people of Russia. 
  "We call on all Russian regions, political parties, 
movements 
and public organisations to leave behind their disagreements and 
join the memorandum on civil peace and accord in Russia in the 
name of peace and prosperity of our motherland." 
  The text of the statement was released by the presidential 
press service. 

</TEXT>

