<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Leaders' Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Leaders' Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104123594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1217 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 21 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin has begun a meeting with the heads of the republics 
which are component parts of the Russian Federation. Opening 
the meeting, he said, "The system of meetings with the republic 
heads is being renewed". 
  According to the president, such meetings with republic 
leaders should be held approximately "five to seven times a 
year". He noted that Thursday's meeting is the first since the 
adoption of a new constitution and the elections to the Federal 
Assembly. 
  "Much has changed in the country in the past few months, 
political stabilisation is gaining strength, the disastrous 
state of dual-power has been overcome", Boris Yeltsin pointed 
out. He also informed the local heads about his work with the 
chairmen of the Federation Council and State Duma, saying that 
there "have been no disagreements so far". 
  On the topic of the recent local elections in Russia, the 
president noted that "the elections were valid in 61 federal 
regions. In only 17 was voter turnout too low". He expressed 
the hope that all the local elections would be held by the end 
of the current year. 

</TEXT>

