<H3> <TI>   EFP Chairman Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EFP Chairman Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2104093094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 Apr 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> MK2104093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [POSTFACTUM report under the "In Brief" rubric] </F>
  [Text] Konstantin Borovoy, chairman of the Economic 
Freedom Party [EFP], has advised that the EFP's attitude to the 
Agreement on Civil Peace will be discussed at the party's 
political council on 28 April. In his view, the signing of the 
agreement would signify a conservation of the status quo, 
whereas "putting today's situation, with all its negative sides 
considered, on ice is a renunciation of the democratic process 
of development." He appreciated the stance of the president who 
seeks accord in society; however, in his words, the EFP "cannot 
give up supporting citizens' interests," that is, waging 
struggle. 

</TEXT>

