<H3> <TI>   Student Organization Regrets Arbat Clashes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Student Organization Regrets Arbat Clashes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2004133494 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2004133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Irina Yuryeva report: "Students Stage Organized Protest"] </F>
  [Text] As we reported, the Russian Association of Trade 
Union Organizations for Students in Higher Educational 
Establishments [RATUOS] staged a picket of the White House 12 
April in order to draw the government's attention once more to 
the plight of the student population. 
  Government staff received representatives of the association 
and a constructive conversation took place between them -- the 
students were promised that the unpaid stipend owed them will be 
paid and measures will be taken to prevent such a thing 
happening in the future. Apart from this, the student leaders 
agreed to meet with Vice Premier Yuriy Yarov. After this the 
student pickets were withdrawn. 
  But representatives of political organizations which use any 
opportunity for self-advertisement remained in the area by the 
White House. After the picket was over, they organized 
themselves into a column and set off for Novyy Arbat, where they 
clashed with the militia. 
  The RATUOS press and information center put out a statement 
from the chairman of its governing body, O. Denisov, expressing 
regret about the participation of several students in the 
unauthorized march but placing most of the blame for what 
happened on representatives of extremist organizations which 
used the students' nonpolitical event for their own purposes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

