<H3> <TI>   Shutdowns at Kola Nuclear Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shutdowns at Kola Nuclear Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104092494 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 0500 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104092494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Murmansk Oblast is on the brink of a power crisis. 
Two power units of the Kola nuclear power station have already 
been shut down. The nuclear power station accounts for 60 
percent of the electricity generated in the region. Engineers 
will have to shut down yet another power unit of the nuclear 
power station in June. The situation in the region may have an 
effect at an all-Russian level, too, because a failure to 
restart all the power units of Kola nuclear power station, which 
supplies power to the Northern Fleet's rear bases and garrisons, 
will adversely affect the fleet's combat readiness. 

</TEXT>

