<H3> <TI>   Shumeyko Calls For Increase in Conscription </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shumeyko Calls For Increase in Conscription </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104103994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0930 
GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2104103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Gondusov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 21 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Russia's revival is 
impossible without the revival of the army. This is what 
Vladimir Shumeyko, chairman of the Federation Council, thinks. 
However, as he stressed today in a conversation with the 
ITAR-TASS correspondent, there can be no question of 
strengthening the army while we are indulging in populist 
gestures and exempting hundreds of thousands of young people 
from army service. 
  Vladimir Shumeyko visited the Taman motorized rifle division 
today. He acquainted himself with the problems of the guards' 
formation, and talked to the servicemen. 
  In keeping with the legislation which is in effect, some 200 
restrictions exist which, according to the speaker of 
parliament's upper chamber, do not allow the army to be manned 
with a sufficiently large contingent of conscripts. "Of 1.5 
million young men, we need to call up at least 700,000, and not 
200,000 which is the current figure. We cannot go on putting up 
with this situation," Vladimir Shumeyko thinks. He noted that a 
"military package" of laws will soon be analyzed in the 
Federation Council in order to introduce changes relating to 
conscription into military service. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

