<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Urges Draft of Pre-Perestroyka Men </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Urges Draft of Pre-Perestroyka Men </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104124294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1150 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Nechayev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (TASS) -- Russian nationalist 
leader Vladimir Zhirinovsky fears the youth today cannot 
decently protect the motherland because of poor health 
undermined by during the years of former Soviet President 
Mikhail Gorbachev and called to recruit men of "older age who 
did not suffer from perestroika in childhood". 
  "The youth today are not like they used to be before 
perestroika. Misery, hunger, life in constant fear for future 
(which began for the kids at nine years of age, that is with 
perestroika years) resulted in that drafted to the army now will 
be weak and sick guys who are unable neither to protect the 
motherland nor themselves", the press service of the Liberal 
Democratic Party said on Thursday quoting Zhirinovskiy. "It is 
possible to recruit up to two million volunteers and let 
children study", the statement reads. 
  Speaking at parliamentary hearings on civic accord 
agreement, 
Zhirinovskiy proposed to the Russian president to cancel his 
decree which stripped students of vocational schools who have 
reached 18 years of age of the right to defer military service. 

</TEXT>

