<H3> <TI>   Gerashchenko: Bank Restrictions May Be Lifted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gerashchenko: Bank Restrictions May Be Lifted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2004113094 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian 20 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2004113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [INTERFAX report: "Restrictions on Foreign Banks' Activity </F>
May Be Lifted"] 
  [Text] Viktor Gerashchenko has said that currently 
"options are being contemplated to lift restrictions on the 
activity of foreign banks in Russia imposed by edict in fall 
1993," and he hopes that this decision may apply not only to 
banks that already had licenses to carry out operations in 
Russia by the time the edict was passed. A spokesman for a 
large Western bank has confirmed that during bilateral meetings 
Russian officials also mentioned the possibility of lifting 
restrictions on the activity of foreign banks in Russia in the 
very near future. Informed Russian sources have also reported 
that a bill on the subject may be submitted to the parliament as 
early as the end of April. 

</TEXT>

