<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karimov Issues Decree on Control of Foreign Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karimov Issues Decree on Control of Foreign Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004215994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1819 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004215994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Uzbek President Islam Karimov has issued a decree on 
regulations of export and import operations in foreign currency. 
The decree provides for an efficient control over currency 
earnings and its utilization when exporting services and 
commodities. 
  In accordance with the decree, Uzbek enterprises and 
organizations cannot settle their accounts on export and import 
with foreign partners through foreign banks. 
  The decree forbids legal entities to sell or pass over the 
quotas on export of services and commodities to other 
participants in the foreign economic activities. The Uzbek 
Ministry of Justice has been proposed to establish juridical 
responsibility of legal entities and individuals for violation 
of the order imposed on export and import operations in foreign 
currency. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

