<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Adilbek Kaipbergenov: "The Sum Does Not Weigh </F>
Down the Pocket"] 
  [Text] The first trading has taken place on the Republic 
currency exchange in Tashkent. In accordance with its results, 
as of 16 April the Central Bank of Uzbekistan established the 
rates for foreign currencies against the national currency. 
Thus, the U.S. dollar is worth 3,637 sum-coupons, and the 
Russian ruble is worth 2.04 (on the black market -- 10). 
  Another item of news -- for the country's guests. As of last 
Saturday, according to an explanation by a Central Bank 
spokesman, they can pay in local bills when buying an air or 
rail ticket, when checking into a hotel, etc., if they present a 
corresponding receipt from a legal exchange point. 

</TEXT>

