<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Crimean Government Takes Office </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Crimean Government Takes Office </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004194094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1608 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004194094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new government of the Ukrainian autonomous 
Republic of Crimea on Wednesday took office in Simferopol. Its 
nucleus is the "Moscow team" of Yevgeniy Saburov, a Russian 
economist invited by Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov to hold the 
post of deputy prime minister. 
  The government includes Economics Minister Andrey 
Chernyavskiy, Finance Minister Lyudmila Zaitseva, Agriculture 
and Food Minister Sergey Nikolskiy, head of the Service of State 
Affairs Viktor Minin, Minister for the Management of State 
Enterprises Anatoliy Franchuk (deputy premier in the previous 
Crimean government), Security Service chief Valeriy Lepikhov, 
Interior Minister Valeriy Kuznetsov, and Justice Minister Lyubov 
Yeliseyeva-Bora. 
  Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk earlier canceled 
Lepikhov's appointment as head of security. 
  All the appointments are subject to confirmation by the 
Crimean parliament. Before that, their titles will be prefixed 
by "acting." 

</TEXT>

