<F P=102>   MK2004110094 Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA in Russian 20 Apr 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MK2004110094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NEZAVISIMAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "NEGA reports" column] </F>
  [Text] Crimea -- Deputies of the Crimean Supreme Soviet 
elected from the Russia bloc as well as deputies supporting the 
bloc's program have held a closed meeting. There are 61 such 
deputies (out of 94). The meeting decided to create a deputies 
group. Deputy Sergey Tsekov, chairman of the Republican Party 
of Crimea, which is affiliated with the Russia bloc, proposed 
that this deputies group fully support the president of the 
Crimean Republic. "Because this group effectively has a 
constitutional majority in the future parliament, any decision 
can be made ignoring the Crimean Tatar deputies (whose number is 
the new parliament is 14)," Tsekov said. This was decisively 
opposed by Vladimir Klychnikov, coordinator of the Russia bloc; 
and deputies Boris Kizilov and Vadim Mordashov. 

</TEXT>

