<H3> <TI>   Repeat Supreme Council Election Set for 24 Jul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Repeat Supreme Council Election Set for 24 Jul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004200094 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 1645 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev -- UNIAN has learned from reliable sources that 
the Central Electoral Commission has ruled the holding of repeat 
elections on 24 July in constituencies where the election was 
invalid or neither of the candidates was elected. A recent 
sitting of Ukraine's Supreme Council presidium proposed to hold 
repeat elections to the Ukrainian Parliament at the same time as 
the second round of local elections, that is, on 10 July. 
However, the Central Electoral Commission has calculated that 
this period would not be long enough for all the stages of 
election envisaged by the electoral law: Nomination and 
registration of candidates, election campaign, etc., of which it 
has informed Ukraine's Supreme Council presidium in writing. 

</TEXT>

