<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze, Turkmen Officials Discuss Gas Payments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze, Turkmen Officials Discuss Gas Payments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004181494 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 1300 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Eduard Shevardnadze, chairman of the Georgian 
parliament and head of State, received Mr. Kananabeldy, first 
deputy chairman of the State Committee for Material and 
Technical Supplies of the Republic of Turkmenistan, who led a 
delegation of Turkmen industrialists on their visit in Tbilisi. 
  The aim of the delegation's visit to Georgia was to choose 
agricultural and industrial products in exchange for Georgia's 
still unpaid debt. The Turkmen side once again showed its full 
understanding of the current complex economic situation in the 
republic, which was reflected in the fact that Georgia will 
supply Turkmenistan with Georgian products in exchange for 3 
billion cubic meters of gas worth several million U.S. dollars, 
as envisaged in the bilateral agreement signed in 1994. 
Meanwhile, our Turkmen friends accepted the prices suggested by 
us. 
  The head of state thanked the Turkmen side for their 
fruitful 
cooperation and understanding of our problems. Shevardnadze 
said: Our republic's population knows very well about your 
realistic support, and we will do everything to carry out our 
responsibilities. 
  At the meeting, Shevardnadze raised the issue of the 
importance of finding new and economically useful ways to 
transport Turkmen gas to Georgia and other countries. 
  Georgian Prime Minister Otar Patsatsia, Deputy Prime 
Minister 
Zurab Kervalishvili, and other officials were present at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

