<H3> <TI>   President Meets NATO Northern Forces Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Meets NATO Northern Forces Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2004124094 Tallinn ETA in English 0822 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2004124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From 20 April PAEVALEHT, EESTI SENUMID, p 1, 3; "News </F>
Bulletin" No. 75/94] 
  [Text] Wednesday, April 20 -- Commander in Chief of the 
NATO Northern group of forces General Garry Johnson met 
President Lennart Meri yesterday. Commander in Chief of the 
Estonian Defence Forces General Aleksander Einseln, General 
Johnson's assistant Colonel Bob Hendicott and aide Captain Tim 
Warrington attended the meeting. 
  General Johnson and President Meri discussed the development 
prospects of the Estonian Defence Forces. General Johnson 
assured that the NATO will further support Estonia. He also 
described the results of his recent visit to Russia. The 
Russian military leaders assured General Johnson that the troops 
will be withdrawn from Estonia in an orderly way and no military 
bases will be established here, the NATO general said. 
  President Meri held a dinner in honour of General and Mrs 
Johnson. 
  The NATO general also met Foreign Minister Juri Luik and 
Defence Minister Indrek Kannik yesterday. They discussed 
Estonian-Russian relations, security in the Baltic region and 
Estonia's cooperation with NATO. 
  General Johnson is to leave Estonia today. 

</TEXT>

