<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Begins Ukraine Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2004135194 Tallinn BNS in English 0922 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2004135194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Apr 20, BNS -- Estonian Defense Minister 
Indrek Kannik and a delegation that includes the head of the 
parliamentary defense commission began a three-day visit to 
Ukraine today. 
  Kannik is to meet his Ukrainian counterpart, Army Gen. 
Vitaliy Radetskyy in the afternoon. The ministers will sign a 
cooperation agreement between the two Defense Ministries in the 
evening. Radetskyy will also give a dinner in honor of the 
Estonian minister. 
  Kannik is scheduled to have meetings with Ukraine's Deputy 
Defense Minister, Col. Gen. Oliynk, the chief of the country's 
army supply division, Col. Gen. Mykhaylychenko, as well as with 
the ministers of Mechanical Industry and Industry. The Estonian 
minister will lay a wreath to the tomb of the Unknown Soldier in 
Kiev later in the day. 
  Friday's [22 April] agenda of the visit includes meetings at 
the Ukrainian Institute of Land Forces and the General Staff. 
  Kannik's delegation includes the chairman of the Estonian 
parliament's defense commission, Rein Helme, the country's 
charge d'affaires in Ukraine, Andrei Birov, Defense Ministry 
Chancellor Tarmo Molder, Defense Ministry and army Central Staff 
officials. 

</TEXT>

