<H3> <TI>   Government Consents to Ethnic Minorities Pact </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Consents to Ethnic Minorities Pact </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2004124394 Tallinn ETA in English 1626 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2004124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn ETA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["News Release"] </F>
  [Text] Estonian Government gave authorities to deputy 
chancellor of the Foreign Ministry Raul Malk to sign an 
agreement between Estonia and Belarus on national minorities, 
Reform Minister Liia Hanni told a press conference on Tuesday 
[19 April]. 
  Hanni said that the agreement will include both Estonian 
nationals that live in Belarus and have Belarusian citizenship 
and Belarusians that have Estonian citizenship. She said that 
the reason the agreement had to be concluded was that there were 
not enough Belarusians in Estonia to grant them rights according 
to the law on cultural autonomy, which gives bigger minorities 
in Estonia rights to found cultural organisations, open schools 
etc. 

</TEXT>

