<H3> <TI>   Russian Citizens League Elects Representative </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Citizens League Elects Representative </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2004113294 Tallinn BNS in English 1849 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2004113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, Apr 19, BNS -- The representative of 
Russian radical nationalist leader Vladimir Zhirinovsky's 
Liberal Democratic party in Estonia, Pyotr Rozhok, was elected 
the chairman of the presidium of Tallinn's League of Russian 
Citizens. 
  The organization of Russian citizens in the Estonian capital 
was established on April 9. 
  Rozhok said the new body is to defend the interests of 
Russian citizen residents of Tallinn. He added that this was to 
be done "only within the limits set by legal acts," by 
bringing, as he said, to the world's notice all violations of 
the rights of Russian citizens in Estonia. The new body is to 
address the United Nations and the Russian parliament on the 
issue in the near future, Rozhok said. 
  He added that there are about 30,000 legal Russian citizens 
living in Tallinn. 
  The organization in Tallinn will also prepare the documents 
necessary for its registration with the Estonian authorities. 
"But I'm more than sure that we will never be registered," 
Rozhok said. 
  The league is also an in corpore member of the Russian 
Community of Estonia, another hardline Russian-speakers' 
organization that has failed so far to gain a formal status with 
Estonia's authorities. 
  More than 42,000 Estonian residents have taken Russian 
citizenship by now. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

