<F P=102>   WS2004135794 Tallinn BNS in English 0922 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2004135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Apr 20, BNS -- The majority of the Saeima 
(parliament) factions' leaders support Latvian President Guntis 
Ulmanis decision to meet with Russian President Boris Yeltsin on 
April 21, Homeland and Freedom faction head Maris Grinblats told 
reporters Tuesday [19 April]. 
  As reported, Russian Ambassador to Latvia Aleksandr Rannikh 
handed over Tuesday to Ulmanis Russian president's invitation to 
meet with him on April 21. 
  Grinblats said it was not yet clear if the signing of the 
Latvian-Russian initialed agreements would be possible during 
this visit. But it is clear already now that the agreement on 
Russian military pensioners' social guarantees will not be 
signed in Moscow, said Grinblats. 
  As reported, the Saeima will decide Wednesday, during its 
extraordinary plenary meeting, if it will authorize Ulmanis to 
sign the initialed Latvian-Russian agreements. 

</TEXT>

