<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protocol Signed Regulating Relations With Norway </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protocol Signed Regulating Relations With Norway </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2104110994 Tallinn BNS in English 1845 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2104110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, Apr 20, BNS -- Albinas Januska, Lithuanian 
deputy foreign minister, and Per Gullik Stavnum, Norway's 
ambassador to Lithuania, on Wednesday [20 April] signed a 
protocol on agreements regulating relations between the two 
countries. 
  The protocol annulled a 1923 agreement on trade and 
navigation and a reciprocal agreement on exempting automobiles 
and other motor vehicles from road taxes, the Lithuanian 
Ministry said. 
  The two pre-war agreements were replaced by a free trade 
agreement and an agreement on international transportation by 
road. 
  A ministry official said the protocol eliminated certain 
legal problems because both pre-war and newly signed agreements 
were considered effective. 

</TEXT>

