<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Antitank Mine Found in Vilnius Square </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Antitank Mine Found in Vilnius Square </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004193894 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Russian 1200 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A fully charged antitank mine was found on Tuesday 
morning on the railroad station square in Vilnius. The police 
received information about the mine at 0645. The fire brigade 
and police blocked all approaches to the railroad station. The 
mine was disarmed. It had been wrapped in a polyethylene bag 
and could explode if touched by a passing vehicle. It took 45 
minutes to eliminate the danger. During this time all 
operations at the Vilnius railroad station were stopped. 
  The police had difficulty shutting trading kiosks as their 
owners, according to policemen, preferred to lose their lives 
than leave their property. 

</TEXT>

