<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Sees Hardening Russian Stance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004221094 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2100 GMT 20 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Lithuanian Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys says 
Russia appears to have hardened its position towards Lithuania. 
The foreign minister, who is visiting Brazil, told the Russian 
ITAR-TASS agency on Wednesday that he knew of no reasons why 
Lithuanian-Russian relations should deteriorate. 
  According to Mr. Gylys, Russia is halting the ratification 
of 
the bilateral agreement on most favored nation status in trade 
signed last autumn. Russia has already granted privileged trade 
terms to 130 countries, however,this does not apply to the 
Baltic states. Lithuania carries out its all commitments to 
Russia and would like Moscow in its turn to observe its 
obligations to Lithuania, said the Lithuanian foreign minister. 

</TEXT>

