<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aushev Urges Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aushev Urges Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004215594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1347 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004215594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ingush President Ruslan Aushev called on Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin to take efficient measures to stabilize 
the situation in the zone of the Ossetian-Ingush conflict. 
Aushev has sent an open letter to Yeltsin emphasizing that the 
decisions by the Russian leadership on normalization of the 
situation and return of refugees and displaced persons to their 
permanent residences are not being implemented. The state of 
emergency in the conflict zone has continued for two years 
already and more than 60,000 refugees cannot return to North 
Ossetia. 
  Aushev said the Moscow talks between the North Ossetian and 
Ingush delegations had brought practically no results. He 
suggested that any further delay in implementation of the 
Russian president's decree on refugees and displaced persons 
issued on December 13, 1993, could trigger off unpredictable 
consequences. 
  Aushev addressed the Russian president as the guarantee for 
human rights in Russia to use all his power in order to prevent 
new inter-ethnic conflicts in North Caucuses. 

</TEXT>

