<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Soldier Killed in N. Ossetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Soldier Killed in N. Ossetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104123694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1149 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (TASS) -- A soldier of the Russian 
Interior Ministry troops was killed early in the morning today 
in the state of emergency zone of North Ossetia. A special-duty 
squad was blasted with fire by a group of armed people near the 
Volchiya mountain at 05.30 today, Andrey Rodnov, spokesman for 
the press service of the task force of the North Caucasian 
Interior Ministry district, told ITAR-TASS from Vladikavkaz. 
The squad was on duty near the villages of Sunzha and Kamgaron 
of the Prigorodniy District, where a number of civilians were 
killed by bandit groups recently and where the provisional 
administration decided to toughen security measures. 
  It is supposed that the bandits were laying mines on the 
road. Shooting started, in the course of which the soldier was 
killed. The bandits disappeared. The provisional administration 
set up a commission for investigating the incident. 
  According to the information released by commander of the 
Russian Interior Ministry troops Colonel Anatoliy Kulikov, in 
1993 areas of provisional deployment of army units and 
special-duty squads in the state of emergency area were fired at 
and attacked 126 times. As a result of it, seven people were 
killed and 133 wounded. This year 20 attacks were staged. 
Today's death of the Russian soldier is the first one this year. 
  The press servce of the Russian Interior Ministry troops is 
not disclosing the name of the soldier in order to avoid 
mistakes, until an official report comes from the command of the 
state of emergency area. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

