<H3> <TI>   Karachay-Cherkesia Defines Border With Georgia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karachay-Cherkesia Defines Border With Georgia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2104083394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 20 Apr 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2104083394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "Border Definition Prepared"] </F>
  [Text] The Karachay-Cherkesia Land Resources Committee has 
prepared a definition of where the line of the state border 
between the Russian Federation and the Republic of Georgia runs 
on Republic of Karachay-Cherkesia territory for discussion at an 
official interstate level. 
  Karachay-Cherkesia and Georgia are neighbors. For many 
decades the border between them has been a symbolic line which 
nobody can guard, running along the inaccessible glacier heights 
of the Main Caucasian Range. But now, with the worsening crime 
threat and the increasing number of refugees and forced 
settlers, the problem of the border, which needs equipping, is 
being discussed by Karachay-Cherkesia as an especially urgent 
one, Oleg Dyba, the head of Karachay-Cherkesia's press 
secretary, noted in a conversation with an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent. 
  In order to further discuss and coordinate where and how the 
border with Georgia should be equipped, the Karachay-Cherkesia 
Council of Ministers has formed a special expert commission, 
taking part in whose work will be specialists of the Russian 
Federation Federal Border Service's "Cherkessk" First 
Independent Border Troops Komendantura and of the Republic of 
Karachay-Cherkesia State Committee for Geology and Mineral 
Utilization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

