<F P=102>   LD2004200194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1915 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004200194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Pavel Vanichkin and Andrey </F>
Loshchilin] 
  [Text] Washington, 20 Apr -- U.S. President Bill Clinton 
has just spoken on the telephone with Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin. The leaders of the two states discussed the current 
situation in Bosnia and measures that the international 
community may take in order to urgently normalize the situation 
