<H3> <TI>   Text of Yeltsin Proposal for Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Text of Yeltsin Proposal for Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2004181594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 21 Apr 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2004181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Text of "Statement of the President of the Russian </F>
Federation": "Boris Yeltsin: `I Confirm the Proposal To Hold a 
Summit Meeting Between Russia, the United States, and the 
European Union and with the Participation of the United 
Nations'"] 
  [Text] "The conflict in Bosnia-Herzegovina is on the brink 
of a dangerous escalation despite Russia's energetic diplomatic 
efforts undertaken jointly with the United Nations and other 
members of the international community. The Bosnian Serb 
leadership must honor the commitments that it made to Russia, 
end the attacks and withdraw from the city of Gorazde, which has 
been declared a "safe area" by the United Nations, ensure the 
conditions for the entry of UN forces there, and end the 
blockade of UN personnel in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  "The world community is called upon to adopt resolute 
measures to achieve a political solution to the Bosnian crisis. 
  "In this connection I confirm the proposal to hold a summit 
meeting between Russia, the United States, and the European 
Union with the participation of the United Nations. 
  "Of course, such a meeting must be thoroughly prepared. The 
corresponding instructions have been given to the Russian 
Federation Foreign Ministry." 
  [Dated] The Kremlin, Moscow, 19 April 1994. 

</TEXT>

