<H3> <TI>   Lord Owen, Stoltenburg Arrive for Talks on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lord Owen, Stoltenburg Arrive for Talks on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Owen on Need To Use Force </H4>

<F P=102> LD2004164594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1400 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004164594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Serov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- Lord Owen, cochairman of the 
conference on the former Yugoslavia, has arrived in Moscow from 
London today. Thorvald Stoltenberg, another representative of 
this forum, is expected to arrive in the Russian capital 
tomorrow. The two diplomats will have talks with Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. The question of Russia's 
participation in political decisionmaking on Bosnia-Herzegovina 
will be at the center of their talks. 
  Russia should take part not only in drawing up the map of 
the 
division of Bosnia-Herzegovina and in the talks regarding 
sanctions against Yugoslavia, but also in adopting resolutions 
on the military actions that the international community should 
be taking in this region, Lord Owen said to journalists before 
his departure for Moscow. The Russians understand that we need 
to use force, he noted, and our key task is to get them on our 
side. What we cannot afford is to allow the UN Security Council 
to be split. 

</TEXT>

