<H4>    Owen, Stoltenberg Favor Quadrilateral Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD2004191894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1841 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By unidentified ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr -- Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev and Lord Owen and Thorvald Stoltenberg, the co-chairmen 
of the coordination committee of the international conference on 
Yugoslavia have spoken in favor of holding urgent consultations 
between special representatives of Russia, the United States, 
the United Nations, and the European Union in order to work out 
a common stance on the Bosnian settlement. They held talks in 
Moscow today. 
  Simultaneously, Kozyrev had a telephone conversation with 
Warren Christopher, suggesting to him that an American 
representative be sent to these quadrilateral consultations. 
The U.S. secretary of state has so far neither accepted nor 
rejected the proposal. 
  The result of the consultations should be a concrete plan 
for 
a postwar structure of Bosnia-Herzegovina. It will then be 
discussed at a quadrilateral summit and presented to the 
conflicting sides. 

</TEXT>

