<DOCNO> FBIS4-17099 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov077_a_94023" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-077 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia Used in `Domestic Political Games' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bosnia Used in `Domestic Political Games' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004192994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1819 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bosnian Serbs are carrying out unthinkable deeds in 
Gorazde, a high-ranking official from the Russian Foreign 
Ministry told Interfax today. 
  "Even brothels have their own rules. However, Bosnian Serbs 
do not recognize them and are "raping" the poor Gorazde in the 
eyes of the whole world," the diplomat said. 
  According to him, the preparedness of many Russian 
parliamentarians to defend Bosnian Serbs only proves that they 
are using the Bosnian crisis as a trump card in their domestic 
political games. "Russian parliamentarians state they are ready 
to wage a war in Bosnia until the death of the last Serb. 
However, this does not make them differ from Serbs who are 
ready to fight until the death of the last Russian," the 
diplomat suggested. 

</TEXT>

