<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Belgrade Officials Deny Russian Envoy Recalled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Belgrade Officials Deny Russian Envoy Recalled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004174794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1630 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004174794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Kondrashov] </F>
  [Text] Belgrade, 20 Apr -- High-ranking diplomats at the 
Russian Embassy in the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia [FRY] have 
denied reports by some of the mass media that Gennadiy Shikin, 
the Russian ambassador to the FRY is being recalled to Moscow 
for consultations. 
  In a conversation today with the ITAR-TASS correspondent 
they 
stated that they know nothing about such plans. What is more, 
they say, the present difficult period requires a redoubling and 
not a weakening of efforts to achieve a settlement of the 
Bosnian crisis. Nor would a reduction of the level of 
diplomatic representation in Yugoslavia be appropriate, since 
the Belgrade leadership is making great efforts to localize the 
conflict around Gorazde and is urging the Bosnian Serb 
leadership to take constructive steps directed at halting the 
bloodshed in the town. 

</TEXT>

