<H3> <TI>   Proposal Forwarded on Division of Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Proposal Forwarded on Division of Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004203594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1819 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004203594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia will put forward a new proposal on division 
of the Black Sea Fleet in accordance with which the strategic 
ships (anti-submarine ships and warships) will belong to Russia 
and the tactical ships (the patrol ones and minesweepers) to 
Ukraine. This was announced to Interfax by reliable sources in 
the Black Sea Fleet headquarters. 
  The same sources said the talks between Russian Defense 
Minister Pavel Grachev and Ukrainian Defense Minister Vitaliy 
Radetskyy in Sevastopol planned for Thursday would focus on 
division of the Black Sea Fleet. 

</TEXT>

