<F P=106> [Unattributed report in the "NEGA reports" column] </F>
  [Text] Within 10 days Ukrainian and Russian delegations 
are to submit to their heads of state a draft agreement on the 
division of the Black Sea Fleet. At a news conference in Kiev, 
Leonid Kravchuk confirmed that he has invited Boris Yeltsin to 
come to Ukraine on an official visit. This visit will take 
place after a large-scale treaty on friendship and cooperation 
has been prepared. The next round of negotiations on the 
division of the Black Sea Fleet is scheduled for 22 April in 
Moscow. Admiral (Ret.) Aleksey Kalinin, former Black Sea Fleet 
commander, expressed his discontent with the agreements reached 
in Moscow on the Black Sea Fleet problem. He stated that none 
of the decisions made in Moscow will satisfy the Black Sea Fleet 
servicemen: "People will relate to it negatively because the 
presidents treat the fleet not an instrument to protect the 
people's interests but as an instrument in political games." 

