<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Text of Yeltsin Statement on Latvian Relations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Text of Yeltsin Statement on Latvian Relations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004173994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1657 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 20 Apr (ITAR-TASS) -- Today, the press 
service of the Russian president released the text of Boris 
Yeltsin's statement. In particular, it says: 
  "The Russian Federation is pursuing a consistent course of 
normalizing its relations with the Latvian Republic and moving 
them onto a footing of good-neighborliness and equal mutually 
advantageous cooperation with a steadfast observance of human 
rights. 
  I believe that the agreements on military matters, which 
were 
initialled this March, create a contractual and legal basis for 
the completion of the withdrawal of Russian troops from the 
territory of Latvia, and for a civilized solution to the issues 
connected with it. They have become possible as a result of 
sensible compromises and responsible approaches and meet the 
true and long-term interests of not merely the peoples of our 
countries, but of the region and Europe as a whole. 
  In this connection, I especially stress that we were not 
going and are not going to create military bases on the 
territory of Latvia. It is a matter only of the temporary 
functioning of one Russian military establishment under civilian 
control -- the radar station in the town of Skrunda. 
  I believe that in the very near future my meeting with 
President G. Ulmanis will take place, during it a package of 
initialled agreements will be signed, and this will become a 
turning point in relations between our countries." 

</TEXT>

