<H3> <TI>   Government Not To Back Down in Latvia Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Not To Back Down in Latvia Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104121794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1117 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova; Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
in English at 1450 GMT on 21 April transmits a service message 
killing this item] 
  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (TASS) -- "We do not find it 
acceptable to remove from the prepared package of documents the 
agreement on social security for military personnel during the 
troop withdrawal" Russian presidential spokesman Vyacheslav 
Kostikov told ITAR-TASS on Thursday, commenting on the results 
of yesterday's session of the Latvian Sejm (Parliament). 
  According to the spokesman, Russia intends to insist that 
all 
of the four prepared documents be signed at the same time. 
Kostikov noted that President Boris Yeltsin, in his scheduled 
telephone conversation today with the Latvian president, might 
touch upon that subject. 
  The Russian spokesman said the Latvian Sejm had been 
"overwhelmed by emotions". He emphasized that Russia is 
interested in continuing the negotiating process with Latvia, 
expressing the hope that "time would solve" such problems. 

</TEXT>

