<H3> <TI>   Estonian Commander, Kolesnikov Discuss Troop Pullout </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Estonian Commander, Kolesnikov Discuss Troop Pullout </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004224994 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1800 
GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2004224994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Major-General Aleksander Einseln, commander of the 
Estonian defense forces, who is on a visit to Moscow, made a 
proposal today to the Russian Ministry of Defense on creating a 
joint working group of the military of the two countries which 
would begin to monitor the withdrawal of Russian troops from 
Estonia. 
  Einseln met today Colonel-General Mikhail Kolesnikov, 
Russian 
chief of general staff. At the meeting ideas were exchanged on 
the activity of the working group on military issues at the 
talks between Estonia and Russia and on the opportunities for 
military collaboration of the two countries. Kolesnikov again 
emphasized that solving the issue of troop withdrawal together 
with giving social guarantees to the retired military living in 
Estonia is important to Russia. 
  As it became known to the Baltic News Service from official 
sources of the Russian Defense Ministry, it was confirmed while 
Kolesnikov and Einseln were meeting that the instruction by 
Boris Yeltsin concerning the creation of Russian military bases 
in the CIS and Latvia was drawn up by the general staff. The 
instruction, issued on 5 April, caused tension between Russia 
and the Baltic states, especially in relations between Latvia 
and Russia. Kolesnikov said that the text of Yeltsin's 
instruction published in ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI did not correspond to 
the truth. Today Kolesnikov (?brought for making public) the 
instruction's actual contents [passage indistinct]. 

</TEXT>

