<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Calls For Immediate End to War in Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Calls For Immediate End to War in Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2104141194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1356 GMT 21 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2104141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Boris Krivoshey and </F>
Aleksandr Krylovich] 
  [Text] Moscow, April 21 (TASS) -- Russia has once again 
called on the warring sides in Rwanda to immediately stop their 
fratricide, put an end to senseless violence and return to the 
practical implementation of the Arusha accord with the 
participation of all political forces, deputy head of the 
Russian Foreign Ministry department of press and information 
Mikhail Demurin said at a briefing today. 
  Any positive motion aimed at an inter-Rwandan settlement 
will 
be met by Russian support and understanding, Demurin noted. "We 
welcome Organization of African Unity (OAU) actions aimed at 
stopping the bloodshed, and hope that joint efforts made by the 
U.N. and the OAU will lead to a turning-point in the present 
dramatic situation in Rwanda. In this connection Moscow 
supports the initiative proposed by the Tanzanian president to 
hold a peace conference on Rwanda in Arusha on April 23," the 
Russian Foreign Ministry official emphasised. 

</TEXT>

