<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Welcomes CIS Decision on Close Integration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Welcomes CIS Decision on Close Integration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004215494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1453 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004215494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anna Melnikova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow April 20 TASS--"For the first time all CIS 
countries have agreed to (pursue) close integration and set up a 
single standing economic commission for economic integration 
between countries," Russian President Boris Yeltsin said at a 
meeting with the heads of Russian regional administrations in 
Moscow on Wednesday. 
  Summing up the results of the CIS summit meeting, Yeltsin 
praised Ukraine's decision to join the economic union as an 
associated member. 
  The CIS leaders adopted decisions on 26 political, economic, 
border, military and international issues. The president noted 
that they had also discussed the situation in trouble spots and 
ways to settle conflicts there. 
  Speaking about the situation in Nagorno-Karabakh and the 
Georgian-Abkhazian conflict, Yeltsin said "there are signs of 
real influence on the settlement of these processes." 

</TEXT>

