<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Finance Minister Relieved of Duties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Finance Minister Relieved of Duties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2004173494 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1608 GMT 20 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2004173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kamchibek Shakirov has been relieved of his duties 
as finance minister for office abuse, sources close to the 
Kyrgyz leadership told INTERFAX. 
  The decision on Shakirov's dismissal was made at a 
government 
presidium meeting yesterday night. At the last session of the 
Republic's parliament which ended on 16 April, Shakirov was 
confronted with the accusation of having granted credits under 
privileged conditions. The Kyrgyz mass media widely publicized 
the fact that Shakirov had granted a soft credit worth 2 million 
sums (Kyrgyz currency) to his son-in-law. 

</TEXT>

